<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3366817>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Aphis fuentesi Nieto Nafría & Ortego, sp. n. A–D apterous viviparous females; A, specimen moderately sclerotized; B, specimen extensively sclerotized; C, dorso-abdominal reticulation; D, siphunculus and marginal tubercles on abdominal segments 6 and 7. F–G, alate viviparous females; F, habitus; G, antennal segment III. H, oviparous female. I, male. The scales vary according to specimens or parts photographed; see measurements in Table 2." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3366817/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

